                    <span>A note to Mr. Kerwick and to "thomasmcgauley" regarding their opinions of The Fitzgeralds and the Kennedys: An American Saga -- to rate a book poorly based on your opinion of the author is not necessarily the purpose of these Spotlight reviews.  These reviews are intended to provide interested readers with information regarding the quality of the work -- and that's where an opinion is involved.  It sounds like you've prejudged this novel according your dislike of the author and subject.  How about an opinion of the book?  Was it well written?  Most certainly.  Was it informative?  You bet.  Would I recommend it to someone who didn't hate the author or the Kennedys and who wanted a riviting account of American history -- it's ups and downs and good and bad?  That's what the stars represent.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">to catch a thief</div>
